    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix deadlock in socket operations due to missing synchronization\n\n### Summary\nThe NAS socket implementation had a critical race condition that could lead to deadlocks when multiple threads accessed the same socket concurrently. This issue was particularly evident in the AS simulator where separate threads handle UE and MME communication.\n\nThe problem occurred because the `socket_id_t` structure was accessed concurrently by multiple threads without proper synchronization, especially when:\n- One thread called `socket_recv` on a SERVER socket (modifying `sid->addr`)\n- Another thread called `socket_send` on the same SERVER socket (reading `sid->addr`)\n\nThis could cause inconsistent lock acquisition ordering and result in deadlocks under certain timing conditions.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/UTIL/socket.c`: Added pthread mutex synchronization around socket structure access\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/UTIL/socket.h`: Added pthread.h include for mutex declarations\n\nThe fix adds a mutex to the socket structure and ensures proper locking in socket_recv and socket_send functions to prevent race conditions.\n"
}